text: Reşit Karabacak (5 July 1954 – 19 November 2020) was a Turkish wrestler. He competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics. Karabacak became European champion in 1983 in Budapest. Karabacak died on 19 November 2020 in Istanbul, Turkey from COVID-19 at the age of 66.Former Turkish wrestler dies of coronavirus ==References== Category:1954 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Olympians for Turkey Category:Turkish wrestlers
